free_txt: Eng.trans.of AE,19,3,1965
Engl.translation of YFI-1.
The authors retreated the experimental
data from AE,19,(1),3,1965 considering resonance
cross section structure and specified absorption
cross section for U-238.
First author A.A.Vankov (=A.A.Van'kov) .
In INDC(CCP)-42,1974 there is no translation of this
article.
Absorption cross section calculation was carried
out from transmission in one-velocity transport
approximation for point neutrons source by Monte-Carlo
method
Corrections were introduced on
* absorption in lead-bismuth alloy (in measurements
with introduction scatterer into sample),
* difference of source from point,
* absorbing properties of neutron source,
* presence of neutrons group with energy 380.keV,
For U-238 samples correction was introduced on U-235
admixture fission.
In water tank case correction was introduced on
absorption of thermal neutrons into sample - ~10%.
4 long counters on distance 1.5-2.mm from source
Water tank with system of fission chambers.
Integrating fission chamber with U-235 layers.
The radical distributions of the neutron flux from the
source in the water were measured by a movable system
of plane fission chamber.Measurements with and without
sample.
Combination of two independent error groups
first group- all errors of experiment and correction
errors
second group- from inaccuracy of the total cross
sections (calculation parameter)
Antimony-beryllium neutron source with external
diameter 3.0 cm and with thickness of beryllium shell
2.mm, 4.mm or 6.mm.
Source intensity near 1.0 x 10**8 neutrons/sec.
Spherical shell transmission
No information.
Spherical layers with internal diameter from
3.0 cm to 10.cm and external diameter from 5.0 cm to
30.cm. A part of samples was prepared from pure
absorbers and a part from absorbers with scatterer-
lead-bismuth alloy.
Numerical data from report Fiz.-Energ institute,
Obninsk,numb.3,Page 14,table 2,1965; the same data
are given in SJA,19,858,1965, except Subent 19.
Final absorption cross sections with errors were
determined by results averaging obtained from long
counter and water tank measurements
Insignificant correction for softening of spectrum into
samples and into source beryllium can was introduced in
final average data.
